WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.211
There's something that you need to know

00:01.234 --> 00:02.429
about the night Chad died.

00:02.454 --> 00:04.054
Eric has your brother's heart.

00:04.078 --> 00:05.984
MAGGIE: <i>What makes
up the sum of a person?</i>

00:06.009 --> 00:07.320
Did you lose somebody, too?

00:07.345 --> 00:08.351
My fiancée.

00:08.376 --> 00:10.960
We rented a motorcycle. I was driving.

00:10.985 --> 00:13.088
<i>Is it the experiences that shape us?</i>

00:13.113 --> 00:15.039
That script of yours, the suicide thing.

00:15.064 --> 00:16.375
That's a tough sell.

00:16.400 --> 00:17.951
<i>Or how we handle them?</i>

00:17.976 --> 00:19.234
Are... Are you s-saying...

00:19.259 --> 00:21.038
I want to adopt a baby.

00:21.063 --> 00:22.832
<i>Even a split-second decision...</i>

00:22.856 --> 00:24.167
- Hey!
- [GROANS]

00:24.191 --> 00:25.296
I'm worried about you.

00:25.321 --> 00:27.756
I saved your life.
You picked me up from jail.

00:27.781 --> 00:28.796
We're even.

00:28.821 --> 00:30.674
<i>... can alter the course of your life.</i>

00:30.699 --> 00:32.984
There is stuff going on with <i>your</i> mom

00:33.009 --> 00:34.485
- that <i>you</i> haven't addressed.
- [LINE RINGS]

00:34.509 --> 00:36.112
<i>And once that ball's in motion...</i>

00:36.137 --> 00:38.248
I haven't been with anyone since Chloe.

00:38.273 --> 00:39.826
<i>... there's no turning back.</i>

00:39.851 --> 00:41.070
I'm gonna tell her.

00:41.095 --> 00:43.140
Now is just not the right time.

00:46.023 --> 00:48.554
♪ Oh, mama, when you give your lovin' ♪

00:48.579 --> 00:51.819
♪ When you give your love,
you drive me crazy ♪

00:51.844 --> 00:54.242
♪ Ah, mama, what you gonna do ♪

00:54.267 --> 00:56.164
- Hello.
- ♪ With all your love in your heart? ♪

00:56.189 --> 00:57.666
May I help you?

00:58.203 --> 01:00.343
[CHUCKLING] Oh, sorry.

01:00.368 --> 01:02.391
This song's kind of impossible
not to sing to, right?

01:02.415 --> 01:05.709
You're gonna use the, uh,
"rhythm's gonna get you" excuse?

01:05.734 --> 01:07.377
[CHUCKLES] Maybe I am.

01:08.428 --> 01:09.703
How much?

01:09.728 --> 01:11.210
I just got engaged, and my fiancé

01:11.235 --> 01:13.476
is going to love and hate these.

01:13.501 --> 01:15.312
For you, $15.

01:15.444 --> 01:17.113
I'll take them.

01:18.427 --> 01:19.726
I-I'll tell you what.

01:19.751 --> 01:21.562
Consider it a wedding gift.

01:21.587 --> 01:23.398
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

01:23.423 --> 01:24.734
Thank you.

01:24.759 --> 01:25.944
[CHUCKLES]

01:25.969 --> 01:27.992
[ <i>MUSIC CONTINUES</i> ]

01:28.017 --> 01:29.585
Good news.

01:29.938 --> 01:31.749
If you like '70s nautical kitsch,

01:31.774 --> 01:33.820
you're gonna love these
salt and pepper shakers.

01:34.014 --> 01:37.367
Oh, perfect.
Cross that off the registry.

01:37.392 --> 01:39.664
Should I, uh...
Should I be worried about you two?

01:39.689 --> 01:40.828
Hey, we're not married yet.

01:40.853 --> 01:42.498
Oh, okay.

01:42.523 --> 01:45.703
♪♪

01:45.728 --> 01:47.375
- Ah, thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

01:47.856 --> 01:49.539
[SIGHS]

01:50.789 --> 01:52.078
[MOTORCYCLE ENGINE STARTS]

01:52.103 --> 01:53.343
- Wow.
- [ENGINE REVS]

01:53.368 --> 01:55.466
You know, I didn't think
I'd be one of those girls

01:55.490 --> 01:57.468
who'd be impressed by
outwardly macho displays,

01:57.492 --> 01:59.101
but I was wrong.

01:59.494 --> 02:01.640
And you wanted to go blueberry picking.

02:01.665 --> 02:04.432
Hey. I like anything that's
both an activity and a snack.

02:04.457 --> 02:05.601
[CHUCKLES] Well, we'll go tomorrow.

02:05.625 --> 02:07.031
- I promise.
- Okay.

02:08.912 --> 02:11.085
- [GRUNTS]
- Gotta do this.

02:12.406 --> 02:13.927
- Aaah!
- Aah!

02:19.771 --> 02:25.176
[CELLPHONE VIBRATING]

02:25.201 --> 02:27.137
[VIBRATING STOPS]

02:32.692 --> 02:37.669
Synced & corrected by QueenMaddie
www.addic7ed.com

02:37.694 --> 02:39.146
WOMAN: <i>Define "tomfoolery"...</i>

02:39.171 --> 02:41.951
It is unbelievable how
low-budget this movie is.

02:41.976 --> 02:45.076
The bailiff just played
the valet in the last scene.

02:45.101 --> 02:46.927
- Did you catch that? Huh?
- [DOOR CLOSES]

02:46.952 --> 02:48.264
- MAN: <i>Objection! Your Honor...</i>
- [SIGHS]

02:48.288 --> 02:49.310
There he is.

02:49.335 --> 02:52.274
Here I am, in my own apartment
that I didn't invite you to.

02:52.299 --> 02:53.497
Give me those keys back,

02:53.522 --> 02:55.857
unless Katherine kicked
you out of the house again.

02:55.882 --> 02:57.911
I guess that was only a matter of time.

02:57.936 --> 03:00.208
Way to roll out the red carpet.

03:00.233 --> 03:01.302
No, actually,

03:01.327 --> 03:03.341
Delilah are I, we're gonna
do a Charlie hand-off,

03:03.366 --> 03:04.904
and since she was in the neighborhood,

03:04.929 --> 03:07.185
we figured we could just... meet here.

03:07.210 --> 03:09.583
Right, 'cause there's not a
Starbucks on every corner.

03:10.794 --> 03:13.505
Dude... is this "Quincy's Lie"?

03:13.530 --> 03:14.827
Why are you doing this to yourself?

03:14.851 --> 03:16.974
Relax. It was in the bargain bin.

03:16.999 --> 03:18.977
Because it is an objectively awful film

03:19.002 --> 03:21.349
filled with '90s tropes
and canned clichés.

03:21.374 --> 03:23.951
<i>... is clearly trying to prey
on the jury's sympathies...</i>

03:23.976 --> 03:25.505
Cue the sage black judge.

03:25.530 --> 03:27.007
JUDGE: <i>I'll allow it, Counselor,</i>

03:27.032 --> 03:29.451
<i>but you better be going
somewhere with this.</i>

03:29.476 --> 03:31.693
[CHUCKLES] I rest my case.

03:31.718 --> 03:33.363
PROSECUTOR: <i>If I could now
turn to page 3...</i>

03:33.387 --> 03:35.411
So, Mom, I'm hoping you'll support me

03:35.436 --> 03:37.388
when I tell you that...

03:38.246 --> 03:41.458
Rome and I have decided to adopt.

03:43.184 --> 03:44.411
- Perfect.
- It's really great.

03:44.436 --> 03:45.630
No, it's not!

03:45.655 --> 03:46.842
'Cause then she's gonna say something

03:46.866 --> 03:49.388
about the miracle of childbirth.

03:49.413 --> 03:51.391
And she's gonna
assume that we're doing it

03:51.416 --> 03:54.263
because we <i>have</i> to,
not because we <i>want</i> to.

03:54.288 --> 03:55.599
Then she'll offer up the number

03:55.624 --> 03:58.396
of a doctor who works miracles with IVF,

03:58.421 --> 04:01.108
all under a passive-aggressive
cloud of "I told you so."

04:01.133 --> 04:02.162
You know, I'm actually starting to think

04:02.186 --> 04:03.569
that your mom and my mom should meet.

04:03.593 --> 04:05.161
I think they'd really hit it off.

04:05.724 --> 04:07.243
Are you two still not talking?

04:07.268 --> 04:09.663
Oh, you mean since she lied
to me about my brother's death

04:09.688 --> 04:11.818
and then chose his
organ recipient over me?

04:11.843 --> 04:13.529
- [SCOFFS]
- So, what's the plan?

04:13.554 --> 04:14.699
You're gonna butter up your mom

04:14.723 --> 04:16.887
with a light lunch and some wine?

04:16.913 --> 04:18.146
That <i>is</i> the plan,

04:18.171 --> 04:20.560
but actually, this is for Gary.

04:20.584 --> 04:23.564
We're gonna go over to his place,
check in on him.

04:23.589 --> 04:25.005
He's just been holed up there

04:25.030 --> 04:27.013
ever since Sophie's
softball game, and...

04:27.038 --> 04:28.841
I think he's embarrassed, and...

04:28.866 --> 04:31.247
Well, he did not seem embarrassed

04:31.272 --> 04:33.318
when I bailed him out of jail.

04:33.771 --> 04:36.622
But hey, things might
go better for you guys.

04:36.647 --> 04:37.661
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

04:37.686 --> 04:39.958
- Eh, it's Eddie.
- [CELLPHONE BEEPS]

04:39.983 --> 04:41.091
Hey.

04:41.116 --> 04:42.130
Are you there already?

04:42.155 --> 04:44.615
Hey, so, uh, what's going on with Eric?

04:44.640 --> 04:46.785
Have you guys had a chance to talk yet?

04:46.810 --> 04:49.288
No. I called, and it went to voicemail.

04:49.313 --> 04:51.333
I think the kiss really scared him off.

04:51.800 --> 04:53.310
So, how bad is it?

04:53.335 --> 04:55.396
[QUIETLY] It's "Quincy's Lie" bad.

04:55.421 --> 04:56.889
[WHISPERING] He's
watching "Quincy's Lie"?

04:56.913 --> 04:58.193
Oh, God.

04:58.218 --> 04:59.319
Are they at the verdict scene yet?

04:59.343 --> 05:00.912
[NORMAL VOICE] Has
the verdict happened yet?

05:00.936 --> 05:02.225
- No, they're at the part where
- Garbage.

05:02.249 --> 05:04.045
the two lawyers get into the fight
near the water fountain.

05:04.069 --> 05:05.755
- You've got 20 minutes.
- <i>20 minutes.</i>

05:05.780 --> 05:07.310
- Yeah, we gotta go.
- Oh.

05:07.335 --> 05:08.849
Okay. W-What is happening?

05:08.874 --> 05:11.435
And what does it have to do with a
'90s courtroom thriller?

05:12.992 --> 05:16.021
Uh... the jury forewoman?

05:16.500 --> 05:18.882
That's Gary's mother.

05:18.907 --> 05:21.099
- Oh.
- He watches it sometimes.

05:21.124 --> 05:23.724
It's like a scab he can't help but pick.

05:24.581 --> 05:25.607
What?

05:25.632 --> 05:26.943
Nothing. No. It's just,

05:26.968 --> 05:28.224
when we were together,

05:28.249 --> 05:29.857
I tried to get him to
talk about his mom,

05:29.882 --> 05:31.919
and it was such a third rail.

05:31.944 --> 05:33.591
They haven't talked since he was a kid.

05:33.616 --> 05:34.833
Yeah, since she left.

05:34.858 --> 05:37.326
No, he... he called her four months ago.

05:37.824 --> 05:38.974
R-Really?

05:38.999 --> 05:40.365
What happened?

05:40.390 --> 05:42.255
Nothing. He hung up right away.

05:43.568 --> 05:45.216
[INHALES SHARPLY]
Looks like we've all got

05:45.241 --> 05:46.708
mommy issues in common.

05:46.896 --> 05:48.964
- Ooh.
- Some of us...

05:48.989 --> 05:50.271
worse than others.

05:50.296 --> 05:51.451
Mm.

05:51.476 --> 05:53.185
Well, on behalf of
all mothers everywhere,

05:53.210 --> 05:54.904
I apologize, ladies.

05:55.615 --> 05:57.716
Now, clean up this stuff. Let's go.

05:57.741 --> 06:01.185
- Oh, God. So much like my mom.
- God. You're so mean.

06:02.179 --> 06:04.911
[CHUCKLES] No, that's great.

06:04.936 --> 06:06.341
- We're good to lock.
- Amazing.

06:06.366 --> 06:07.701
I mean, soft lock.

06:07.726 --> 06:10.302
Yeah, Gene hasn't texted me... back.

06:10.327 --> 06:11.805
But, uh, he's gonna love it.

06:11.830 --> 06:15.436
I just need to hear him say that, so...

06:15.461 --> 06:17.732
Oh, congratulations, by the way.

06:17.757 --> 06:19.177
- For what?
- What?

06:19.202 --> 06:20.428
What do you mean,
"For what"? Come on, man.

06:20.452 --> 06:21.685
For selling your movie.

06:21.710 --> 06:23.435
Yeah, it's all over the trades.

06:23.974 --> 06:25.684
A-At least I thought it was your movie.

06:25.709 --> 06:27.083
The log-line sounded like yours,

06:27.108 --> 06:28.810
and your producer friend is attached.

06:28.835 --> 06:30.354
Todd Pilsner?

06:30.379 --> 06:32.005
Wait.

06:32.030 --> 06:33.521
For real?

06:33.546 --> 06:35.402
You know what? Forget
I even said anything.

06:35.427 --> 06:38.255
I just kind of skimmed it,
and, uh, I'm probably wrong.

06:38.280 --> 06:39.549
I'm... I'm frequently wrong.

06:39.574 --> 06:41.560
That's what, uh...
That's what Gene always says.

06:42.497 --> 06:45.544
Totally forgotten, brah. [CHUCKLES]

06:45.569 --> 06:48.286
- <i>Um, this trial illuminates...</i>
- Look at that.

06:48.311 --> 06:50.255
Juror Number Seven...
she's knitting, right?

06:50.280 --> 06:52.177
She just took the yarn
ball out of her purse

06:52.202 --> 06:53.529
in the last scene,

06:53.554 --> 06:54.560
and look.

06:54.585 --> 06:56.029
It's an entire sweater.

06:56.054 --> 06:57.657
Who's on continuity?!

06:58.155 --> 06:59.577
- <i>This trial is different.</i>
- [DOOR OPENS]

06:59.601 --> 07:01.474
Ah! Look who's here.

07:01.499 --> 07:02.716
- Hi!
- Charlie.

07:02.741 --> 07:04.177
- How's my girl?
- Did we miss it?

07:04.202 --> 07:05.202
Moments away.

07:05.227 --> 07:07.202
The stenographer just winked
at the defense counsel.

07:07.226 --> 07:09.216
It really takes you out when you realize

07:09.241 --> 07:13.099
that the "expert witness,"
the lynchpin to the whole case,

07:13.124 --> 07:15.365
is the "fence-is-covering
half-my-face" guy

07:15.390 --> 07:16.833
from "Home Improvement."

07:19.144 --> 07:20.955
Hey, babe, how'd it go?

07:21.175 --> 07:22.175
- Uh...
- What's wrong?

07:22.200 --> 07:23.740
Oh, nothing. It's... It's, um...

07:23.765 --> 07:26.326
It's probably nothing,
and it's not why we're here.

07:26.351 --> 07:28.497
Gary, my man. How we doing?

07:28.947 --> 07:31.116
Look at that. The gang's all here.

07:31.870 --> 07:33.271
Why is the gang all here?

07:33.296 --> 07:34.669
I-I personally was...

07:34.694 --> 07:35.990
- Shh, shh!
- BAILIFF: <i>All rise.</i>

07:36.015 --> 07:37.701
Uh, uh, uh. Shh, shh, shh, shh.

07:37.726 --> 07:39.829
JUDGE: <i>Has the jury reached a verdict?</i>

07:39.854 --> 07:46.854
♪♪

07:48.796 --> 07:50.443
[ <i>GASPS</i> ]

07:51.888 --> 07:53.927
You were just in the deliberation room.

07:53.952 --> 07:55.763
Why do you look surprised?

07:55.788 --> 08:02.788
♪♪

08:02.946 --> 08:04.257
<i>Guilty.</i>

08:04.282 --> 08:06.001
- [SCOFFS]
- DEFENDANT'S WIFE: <i>No! It's a lie!</i>

08:06.025 --> 08:07.368
- [ <i>GAVEL BANGS</i> ]
<i>- You can't do this to him!</i>

08:07.392 --> 08:08.704
JUDGE: <i>Order! Order in the court!</i>

08:08.728 --> 08:10.985
- <i>I said order!</i>
- Okay. Yeah. I think we're done here.

08:11.997 --> 08:13.474
- <i>Order in the court!</i>
- Bye-bye.

08:13.499 --> 08:14.937
- [TV SHUTS OFF]
- Hey! Hey, D! What are you doing?

08:14.961 --> 08:17.233
This is not healthy, Gary.

08:17.258 --> 08:19.256
Just because you're
out of kids to mother

08:19.281 --> 08:21.459
doesn't mean you get to
scratch that itch with me.

08:21.484 --> 08:22.514
EDDIE: Hey. No, no, no.

08:22.539 --> 08:24.467
Gary, you do not get to say that to her.

08:24.499 --> 08:27.092
I didn't invite you here... any of you.

08:27.117 --> 08:29.858
You ambushed me in my own home.

08:29.883 --> 08:32.428
You don't like what I have to say,
there's the door.

08:34.820 --> 08:36.693
- No. I'll go talk to him.
- [DOOR OPENS]

08:36.717 --> 08:38.076
Hey, what's your plan here?

08:38.101 --> 08:39.928
You just gonna keep pushing people away

08:39.953 --> 08:41.842
until there's no one left?

08:42.861 --> 08:44.522
You know, at a certain point, Gary,

08:44.547 --> 08:46.131
the problem isn't everyone else.

08:46.156 --> 08:48.381
The problem is you.

08:49.090 --> 08:51.154
You think I don't know that?

08:51.179 --> 08:55.483
♪♪

08:55.508 --> 08:57.611
Maggie said you called your mother.

08:57.636 --> 08:59.100
Yeah.

08:59.321 --> 09:01.678
And then I hung up because
I don't want to talk to her.

09:01.703 --> 09:03.311
Well, you might not want to talk to her,

09:03.336 --> 09:06.037
but maybe... you need to.

09:08.068 --> 09:09.717
[SIGHS]

09:11.074 --> 09:13.850
- Unbelievable.
- What's up?

09:13.875 --> 09:16.045
I really think Todd stole my movie.

09:16.070 --> 09:18.217
What? No. You and Todd go way back.

09:18.242 --> 09:19.381
He wouldn't do that.

09:19.406 --> 09:20.788
Okay, well, how do you explain this?

09:20.812 --> 09:23.639
"When a serious sports injury
leaves one of them paralyzed,

09:23.664 --> 09:25.116
four friends get the
wake-up call they need

09:25.140 --> 09:27.288
to stop waiting for tomorrow
and start living for today"?

09:27.312 --> 09:28.980
Whoa.

09:29.546 --> 09:31.865
Well, did you ask him about it?
What did he say?

09:31.890 --> 09:33.726
Nothing. Dude's been
dodging my calls all morning.

09:33.750 --> 09:35.398
[SIGHS] I don't even
know where the woman is.

09:35.422 --> 09:36.615
I do.

09:36.640 --> 09:38.006
I looked her up on the way over.

09:38.031 --> 09:39.675
She's in Brooklyn, starring in a play

09:39.700 --> 09:41.443
called "The Summer Place."

09:42.458 --> 09:43.686
Well, that's great,

09:43.711 --> 09:46.709
but I can't just drop everything
and go to New York, D.

09:46.734 --> 09:47.740
You're going to New York?

09:47.765 --> 09:49.409
I just said I'm <i>not</i>
going to New York.

09:49.434 --> 09:50.881
Todd's in New York. I'll come with.

09:50.906 --> 09:51.951
Is no one listening to me?

09:51.976 --> 09:54.139
Gary, if not now, then when?

09:55.658 --> 09:57.177
I'll go on a road trip with you.

09:57.202 --> 09:58.221
I love road trips,

09:58.246 --> 10:00.349
and Danny's at a sleepover all weekend,

10:00.374 --> 10:01.412
Charlie's with Eddie,

10:01.437 --> 10:03.600
and, as you so kindly
pointed out, Sophie's...

10:03.625 --> 10:05.045
I'm sorry.

10:05.773 --> 10:07.693
I shouldn't have said that.

10:08.168 --> 10:10.498
Don't be sorry. Just come with us.

10:10.523 --> 10:12.647
♪♪

10:12.672 --> 10:14.149
[SIGHS]

10:14.174 --> 10:17.279
♪♪

10:17.304 --> 10:18.615
Alright. I'll go.

10:19.655 --> 10:21.631
But I'm gonna get out ahead of this...

10:22.302 --> 10:24.342
No French music.

10:24.367 --> 10:25.920
[CHUCKLES]

10:28.211 --> 10:29.967
[TAPE RIPS]

10:30.651 --> 10:31.990
Eric?

10:33.487 --> 10:35.506
Eric, come on. I can hear you.

10:35.531 --> 10:37.342
[LOCK DISENGAGES]

10:37.367 --> 10:38.740
- Hey.
- Hi.

10:38.765 --> 10:41.443
Sorry to just show up like this,

10:41.468 --> 10:44.763
but I felt like we really
needed to talk about...

10:46.540 --> 10:48.264
Hey, what's going on?

10:48.944 --> 10:50.623
Are you m-moving?

10:50.648 --> 10:52.459
[SIGHS]

10:52.484 --> 10:56.514
♪♪

10:56.539 --> 11:01.479
♪♪

11:01.503 --> 11:03.026
Oh, my God.

11:03.051 --> 11:05.196
This is... This is totally my movie.

11:05.221 --> 11:07.683
The story, the characters...

11:07.708 --> 11:09.354
Well, Todd's version of it.

11:09.379 --> 11:11.448
Wait, that's the script?
How did you get that?

11:11.473 --> 11:14.425
Assistants talk and they share and...

11:14.537 --> 11:16.229
They're calling his "Unseen."

11:16.254 --> 11:18.058
My script is called "Invisible."

11:18.175 --> 11:19.980
Dude, look at this line
from the Gil character.

11:20.004 --> 11:22.847
Look at that. "It's not that
I don't have cancer.

11:22.872 --> 11:25.573
It's that I don't
<i>currently</i> have cancer."

11:26.067 --> 11:28.713
Taking my words and making them worse.

11:28.738 --> 11:30.549
Technically <i>my</i> words.

11:30.743 --> 11:33.237
And "Gil"? Really, man?

11:33.442 --> 11:35.378
Is that all you're getting from this?

11:35.806 --> 11:38.618
[JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS]

11:39.399 --> 11:40.399
Hi.

11:40.424 --> 11:42.487
I'm here to meet my mom,
but I'm a little late.

11:42.512 --> 11:44.940
Uh... which I'm sure will
be what she opens with.

11:44.965 --> 11:46.128
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

11:46.153 --> 11:47.448
Well, you're safe.

11:47.473 --> 11:49.206
Doesn't look like she's arrived yet.

11:49.231 --> 11:50.261
Oh. Yoo-hoo!

11:50.286 --> 11:51.542
Oh, there she is.

11:51.567 --> 11:54.768
I'm so sorry.
I didn't realize she was your...

11:54.793 --> 11:56.870
- That's okay.
- Sweetie! There you are.

11:56.895 --> 11:59.082
Oh! I was about to
send out a search party.

11:59.107 --> 12:01.917
- [BOTH CHUCKLE]
- Yep, that's my mom.

12:04.801 --> 12:06.503
[SIGHS]

12:07.212 --> 12:08.901
You okay over there?

12:09.123 --> 12:12.073
Honestly, I'm starting
to rethink this whole plan.

12:12.098 --> 12:13.347
Okay? There's...

12:13.372 --> 12:15.870
There's... There's nothing she
can say to justify what she did.

12:15.895 --> 12:18.498
Well, maybe it's not about what
<i>she</i> says to <i>you.</i>

12:18.523 --> 12:21.460
Maybe it's about what <i>you</i>
finally get to say to <i>her.</i>

12:21.558 --> 12:24.245
Like, "How the hell could
you abandon a 7-year-old?"

12:25.889 --> 12:28.058
[SIGHS]

12:28.083 --> 12:30.847
So, now we're the proud
pseudo-parents of a 16-year-old

12:30.872 --> 12:32.933
who, apparently, is physically incapable

12:32.958 --> 12:35.269
- of doing her own laundry.
- [CHUCKLES]

12:35.510 --> 12:38.347
But it is wonderful you two stepped in.

12:40.461 --> 12:44.448
Yeah, we've actually
been thinking a lot this year

12:44.473 --> 12:47.339
about what family means, and, well...

12:47.740 --> 12:51.511
Rome and I have made
kind of a big decision,

12:51.536 --> 12:54.182
a decision that may surprise you.

12:54.666 --> 12:56.659
Oh, my God. It...

12:56.684 --> 12:58.104
We're adopting.

12:58.980 --> 13:00.729
We're having a baby!

13:00.754 --> 13:02.323
- [CHUCKLES]
- Ooh.

13:02.348 --> 13:03.690
Well... Well, we...

13:03.715 --> 13:05.987
We feel, as a couple, that adoption is

13:06.012 --> 13:07.426
- the right choice for us.
- Yes, yes.

13:07.450 --> 13:09.878
I heard you. Adoption is incredible.

13:09.903 --> 13:12.893
I mean, it's all of the joy
and none of the stretch marks.

13:13.216 --> 13:15.276
Now get to the good part... boy or girl?

13:15.301 --> 13:16.972
Oh, I hope it's a girl.

13:16.997 --> 13:19.100
Oh, a little tomboy, just like you were,

13:19.125 --> 13:20.893
just always playing in the dirt.

13:20.918 --> 13:23.018
Or a boy. I mean, hmm, who am I kidding?

13:23.043 --> 13:25.127
Either way, it is a grandbaby.

13:25.152 --> 13:26.796
Oh, Gina.

13:26.821 --> 13:28.799
♪♪

13:28.824 --> 13:30.206
So...

13:30.231 --> 13:34.348
were you just gonna
leave and not tell me?

13:34.373 --> 13:37.235
No. No. I, uh... [SIGHS]

13:37.260 --> 13:38.992
I don't know. I...

13:40.496 --> 13:41.578
It's just that living

13:41.603 --> 13:43.248
in the same apartment
I shared with Chloe,

13:43.273 --> 13:45.960
running her store... It's...
it's hard to move on

13:45.985 --> 13:49.131
when she's everywhere I turn, you know?

13:49.209 --> 13:50.656
Yeah. I do.

13:50.681 --> 13:53.046
Plus, there's this lawsuit.

13:53.071 --> 13:55.742
Chloe's parents blame me for her death.

13:56.302 --> 13:58.609
And they're right.

13:58.820 --> 14:00.799
I mean, she didn't even want
to go for a ride that day.

14:00.823 --> 14:02.304
She wanted to go blueberry picking.

14:02.329 --> 14:04.453
You can't do that to yourself.

14:04.478 --> 14:05.913
Believe me, I've been there.

14:05.938 --> 14:07.274
There are so many things I've done

14:07.298 --> 14:09.171
that I wish I could take back,

14:09.196 --> 14:11.062
and I just want a fresh start.

14:13.567 --> 14:15.378
[INHALES DEEPLY, SIGHS]

14:15.403 --> 14:17.882
Look, I'm so sorry
about the other night,

14:17.907 --> 14:20.984
and I didn't call sooner because...

14:21.266 --> 14:24.593
I think I just needed
to process everything.

14:26.136 --> 14:27.562
But this is...

14:27.587 --> 14:28.882
- Complicated.
- Yeah.

14:28.907 --> 14:32.053
And not just because
of everything with Gary

14:32.078 --> 14:35.695
or the fact that you're
trying to get over Chloe, but...

14:36.487 --> 14:38.703
I mean, you have my brother's heart.

14:38.728 --> 14:40.015
♪♪

14:40.040 --> 14:41.999
And at first...

14:42.936 --> 14:45.163
that's what it was.

14:45.188 --> 14:46.957
But, honestly, I would be lying

14:46.982 --> 14:49.406
if I said that there wasn't...

14:49.927 --> 14:51.663
something here.

14:51.688 --> 14:54.320
♪♪

14:54.345 --> 14:56.782
Am I wrong? I mean, is it just me?

14:58.058 --> 14:59.535
No.

14:59.560 --> 15:01.246
[INHALES DEEPLY]

15:01.271 --> 15:03.634
No, it's not just you.

15:03.659 --> 15:08.259
♪♪

15:08.284 --> 15:10.173
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

15:10.198 --> 15:12.118
I don't understand.

15:12.143 --> 15:14.376
Why are you leaving?

15:14.788 --> 15:18.095
Don't you think that Chloe
would want this for you?

15:18.120 --> 15:20.376
Don't you think she would
want you to try to move on?

15:20.401 --> 15:23.964
It's... It's not that simple. [SIGHS]

15:24.729 --> 15:26.657
MAGGIE: Wait, what is this?

15:29.662 --> 15:30.782
- It's 2017.
- Maggie.

15:30.807 --> 15:32.649
- Wait. Whoa.
- Maggie, don't. Don't.

15:33.337 --> 15:35.290
Where is your scar?

15:35.315 --> 15:37.079
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

15:37.104 --> 15:42.088
Grief has a way of making people
do [ECHOING] crazy things.

15:42.732 --> 15:44.611
GARY: <i>Trust me.</i>

15:44.636 --> 15:47.213
There is something off about that guy.

15:47.238 --> 15:48.683
I don't trust him,
and you shouldn't either.

15:48.707 --> 15:50.604
- ERIC: <i>Trust me.</i>
- GARY: <i>I don't trust him.</i>

15:50.629 --> 15:51.940
[EXHALES SHAKILY]

15:51.965 --> 15:53.525
Oh, my God.

15:53.550 --> 15:56.070
Maggie, just please let me explain.

15:56.095 --> 15:58.588
[EXHALES SHAKILY]

15:58.613 --> 16:00.549
Maggie, wait.

16:00.574 --> 16:02.218
[DOOR SLAMS]

16:02.243 --> 16:07.541
♪♪

16:07.565 --> 16:09.744
He'll be with you in a few.
He's just finishing up on a call.

16:09.768 --> 16:11.088
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

16:11.113 --> 16:12.947
TODD: Avery, make me and Isaac

16:12.972 --> 16:15.172
a reservation tonight
at Hawthorne Place.

16:15.197 --> 16:16.751
On it!

16:16.775 --> 16:18.502
Isaac? Like Isaac Martin?

16:18.527 --> 16:21.010
I know. It's so exciting. [CHUCKLES]

16:21.279 --> 16:22.416
Wow.

16:23.611 --> 16:25.229
Dude.

16:25.254 --> 16:27.107
An office pop-in?
What are... What are...

16:27.132 --> 16:28.447
What are you doing here?

16:28.909 --> 16:30.094
[SIGHS]

16:30.119 --> 16:31.596
What am I doing here?

16:32.752 --> 16:35.713
I came to find out why
you stole my movie.

16:35.738 --> 16:38.050
- ALICE: Okay.
- WOMAN: You're amazing.

16:38.075 --> 16:40.165
- Thank you.
- Thank you. Thank you.

16:40.190 --> 16:41.252
You okay?

16:41.277 --> 16:42.901
- Hi.
- Hi. Come on in.

16:42.926 --> 16:44.807
- Such a pleasure.
- Thank you.

16:45.026 --> 16:47.362
Okay, there we go.

16:47.386 --> 16:48.386
- Great.
- Thanks.

16:48.411 --> 16:50.479
Tell your friends. Come back.

16:50.504 --> 16:52.213
Hi. Who should I make it out to?

16:52.238 --> 16:54.674
- Make it to Gary.
- Okeydoke.

16:54.699 --> 16:56.511
Gary Mendez.

16:56.536 --> 16:59.072
♪♪

16:59.097 --> 17:00.518
Oh, my God.

17:02.171 --> 17:03.518
Gary.

17:04.295 --> 17:05.940
[DOOR CLOSES]

17:05.964 --> 17:08.944
[SIGHS]

17:09.428 --> 17:11.118
You don't know how many times

17:11.144 --> 17:13.289
I have dreamt about this moment.

17:13.314 --> 17:14.932
Cut the theatrics, Alice.

17:14.957 --> 17:16.627
You're not on stage.

17:16.652 --> 17:19.010
You don't get to pretend to care.

17:19.035 --> 17:20.222
You lost that right when you left.

17:20.246 --> 17:22.268
But you have to understand, Gary...

17:23.525 --> 17:25.086
... I was 18

17:25.111 --> 17:27.400
when I discovered that
I was pregnant with you.

17:27.425 --> 17:29.471
I tried to be a good mother.

17:29.496 --> 17:32.893
For seven years... I tried.

17:32.918 --> 17:37.385
But the whole time,
I was drowning inside.

17:38.629 --> 17:41.963
I know... it was selfish.

17:42.931 --> 17:43.954
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

17:43.979 --> 17:46.025
But I thought about you every day.

17:46.050 --> 17:47.439
Yeah, right.

17:48.242 --> 17:49.844
You left, and you never came back.

17:49.869 --> 17:51.494
No, you're wrong.

17:51.975 --> 17:53.736
I did come back.

17:55.713 --> 17:58.025
Stop playing with me.
You know exactly what you did.

17:58.050 --> 17:59.729
What are you talking about?

17:59.754 --> 18:01.416
I said, "Let's do a sports movie."

18:01.441 --> 18:03.861
You said no. You turned me down.

18:03.886 --> 18:05.354
But I knew my idea was good,

18:05.379 --> 18:06.979
so I set it up with a different writer.

18:07.004 --> 18:08.908
It's not <i>your</i> idea. It's <i>my</i> idea.

18:08.933 --> 18:11.572
You wanted to do some
sad movie about suicide.

18:11.597 --> 18:13.869
I am doing an uplifting sports movie.

18:13.894 --> 18:16.039
You were just on the
phone with Isaac Martin.

18:16.064 --> 18:18.375
I pitched to Isaac for
the lead over lunch.

18:18.400 --> 18:20.666
Oh, come on, Rome.
Isaac is hot right now.

18:20.691 --> 18:23.111
You can't honestly
think that was your idea.

18:23.136 --> 18:24.846
Dude, do you... do you hear yourself?

18:24.871 --> 18:27.611
I came here to understand how
you could do what you did,

18:27.636 --> 18:29.807
and if you can't even admit it,

18:29.832 --> 18:31.811
well, maybe I just need to
get my attorneys involved.

18:31.835 --> 18:35.439
You know as well as I do
you can't copyright an idea.

18:35.865 --> 18:37.697
But hey, if that's what you need to do,

18:37.722 --> 18:40.291
maybe my law firm could
finally earn their retainer.

18:40.316 --> 18:41.502
Good line.

18:41.527 --> 18:43.197
You steal that one, too?

18:43.222 --> 18:45.158
[SCOFFS]

18:45.460 --> 18:47.158
You know...

18:47.183 --> 18:48.557
ever since film school,

18:48.582 --> 18:50.101
you were the guy with the good ideas

18:50.126 --> 18:52.010
that only lived in your head.

18:52.035 --> 18:54.072
You always talked about
making a movie for years,

18:54.097 --> 18:56.494
and yet... nothing.

18:57.270 --> 18:58.846
At least now you can take solace

18:58.871 --> 19:01.627
in knowing that this
will actually get made.

19:01.652 --> 19:03.174
♪♪

19:03.199 --> 19:07.111
Now, if you'll excuse me,
got another meeting.

19:07.136 --> 19:10.447
♪♪

19:10.472 --> 19:11.799
[GASPS]

19:11.824 --> 19:13.010
Oh.

19:13.035 --> 19:14.494
Oh, my goodness. Oh, my goodness.

19:14.519 --> 19:15.666
It's a wittle wabbit.

19:15.691 --> 19:16.835
- [LAUGHS]
- Oh.

19:16.860 --> 19:18.783
Oh, honey, we are getting this.

19:18.808 --> 19:20.393
Okay. Well, it's adorable,

19:20.418 --> 19:22.563
but let's not get ahead of ourselves.

19:22.588 --> 19:24.233
We don't know if it's
gonna be a boy or a girl

19:24.257 --> 19:26.069
or a baby or a toddler.

19:26.094 --> 19:28.322
Ooh! I know. We will start a registry.

19:28.347 --> 19:29.825
Uh, just pick everything you want,

19:29.850 --> 19:31.230
and we'll narrow it down later. Yes?

19:31.254 --> 19:33.471
- I'm gonna get the girl.
- Okay. Um, Mom.

19:33.496 --> 19:35.974
Mom, it's fine.
You don't have to do this.

19:35.999 --> 19:37.127
Of course I do.

19:37.152 --> 19:38.355
Do you know how long I've been waiting

19:38.379 --> 19:39.955
to spoil a grandchild?

19:40.300 --> 19:42.088
Hello. We would like
to start a registry,

19:42.113 --> 19:43.479
and we need...

19:44.101 --> 19:45.760
everything... everything.

19:45.785 --> 19:48.416
And, um, organic only
and gender-neutral colors.

19:48.441 --> 19:50.307
- Okay.
- Who's woke? [CHUCKLING] Me.

19:50.332 --> 19:52.416
SALESWOMAN: Okay. Let's do this.

19:52.441 --> 19:55.439
And if you're going for neutral,
green is the new yellow.

19:55.464 --> 19:57.049
- I'll pull some pieces.
- Thank you.

19:57.074 --> 19:58.218
I love green.

19:58.243 --> 20:00.635
You know, I thought you might have...

20:00.859 --> 20:03.525
a problem with us adopting.

20:03.550 --> 20:05.361
You kidding me?

20:05.457 --> 20:07.744
Honey, I am thrilled.

20:07.769 --> 20:10.456
I just hope you two don't
have to wait too long.

20:10.481 --> 20:13.869
When Becky's daughter adopted,
they had to wait two years.

20:13.894 --> 20:15.674
Eh. Of course, they insisted

20:15.699 --> 20:17.166
- the baby look like them.
- [SIGHS]

20:17.582 --> 20:19.783
Yeah, well, I understand that.

20:19.808 --> 20:22.814
Growing up, I just wanted to fit in.

20:22.839 --> 20:23.861
But it was tough,

20:23.886 --> 20:26.111
'cause I didn't feel black enough,

20:26.136 --> 20:28.072
definitely didn't feel white enough.

20:28.312 --> 20:31.979
Rome and I have been talking
a lot about that lately,

20:32.004 --> 20:35.557
about adopting a
baby that looks like us,

20:35.582 --> 20:37.557
that's part of our community.

20:38.774 --> 20:40.439
Oh.

20:40.464 --> 20:42.236
I see.

20:42.568 --> 20:44.885
No, Mom, I didn't mean to...

20:44.910 --> 20:46.650
No, no, no, Gina.

20:46.675 --> 20:48.486
I know exactly what you meant.

20:48.965 --> 20:51.283
[SINGSONG VOICE] Who likes chartreuse?

20:51.308 --> 20:54.236
♪♪

20:54.261 --> 20:55.363
What are you talking about?

20:55.388 --> 20:57.119
After you left, I never saw you again.

20:57.144 --> 20:58.252
No.

20:58.277 --> 21:00.104
But I saw <i>you.</i>

21:00.408 --> 21:02.697
I came back a year later.

21:02.722 --> 21:05.541
I had to make sure you were okay.

21:05.566 --> 21:07.549
When I pulled up to the house,

21:07.574 --> 21:09.386
I saw you at the end of the street.

21:09.689 --> 21:11.932
You were playing hockey
with all your friends.

21:11.957 --> 21:14.533
I watched the whole game.

21:14.558 --> 21:17.768
You scored two goals
against Alec Denning.

21:20.148 --> 21:21.918
You were there.

21:22.106 --> 21:23.111
Why didn't you, uh...

21:23.136 --> 21:25.588
When I saw you with all your friends,

21:25.613 --> 21:28.354
you seemed so happy.

21:28.379 --> 21:31.900
Somehow, without me,
you'd made yourself whole again,

21:31.925 --> 21:33.839
and I knew if I got out of that car,

21:33.864 --> 21:35.582
I would wreck that.

21:37.422 --> 21:39.608
So I left.

21:39.741 --> 21:42.175
"Made myself whole"?

21:42.460 --> 21:43.896
What does that even mean?

21:43.921 --> 21:45.399
Like, in all the ways in which I was

21:45.424 --> 21:46.636
missing something in my life,

21:46.661 --> 21:48.575
I didn't want you to feel like
you were missing something, too.

21:48.599 --> 21:50.714
I was missing my mother.

21:51.777 --> 21:55.472
What I was missing was my mother.

21:56.689 --> 21:58.652
I smiled with some friends,

21:58.677 --> 22:00.269
and that was enough to convince you

22:00.294 --> 22:02.011
that I didn't need you?

22:03.171 --> 22:05.410
You want to know
what that year was like?

22:05.435 --> 22:06.912
I'll tell you.

22:07.039 --> 22:08.517
Every day for weeks,

22:08.542 --> 22:10.554
I asked Dad when you were coming back.

22:10.579 --> 22:14.655
He said, "Soon, Gare.
She just needs some time."

22:16.296 --> 22:18.147
Even after you abandoned us,

22:18.172 --> 22:20.608
he was lying to protect <i>you.</i>

22:20.633 --> 22:23.843
Weeks turned into months.

22:23.868 --> 22:26.114
[CHUCKLES] Finally, I stopped asking

22:26.139 --> 22:29.767
because I realized that
it was tearing him apart.

22:30.964 --> 22:32.632
And then one day...

22:33.302 --> 22:36.061
- I'm watching some movie.
- [CHAIR SLAMS]

22:36.086 --> 22:38.741
Dad walks in and turns white as a ghost.

22:38.766 --> 22:39.960
I don't understand why,

22:39.985 --> 22:42.631
until I see you in that jury box.

22:43.366 --> 22:46.100
And right then, I knew
you were never coming back.

22:46.125 --> 22:49.194
♪♪

22:49.219 --> 22:50.764
You were better off without me.

22:50.789 --> 22:53.468
You saw what you <i>wanted</i> to see.

22:53.493 --> 22:55.155
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

22:55.180 --> 22:56.327
JOSH: Alice, I'm sorry...

22:56.352 --> 22:58.546
- Two minutes, Josh.
- Nah, I'm out of here.

22:58.571 --> 22:59.773
- No, no, no, no. Wait. W-Wait.
- I-I'll go.

22:59.797 --> 23:01.811
Please, just give us a second.

23:01.991 --> 23:03.124
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

23:03.149 --> 23:04.741
I'm sorry.

23:08.475 --> 23:10.311
[VOICE BREAKING] I'm sorry.

23:12.762 --> 23:14.897
Can... Can we try again?

23:15.592 --> 23:18.147
[INHALES SHAKILY, EXHALES SHARPLY]

23:18.172 --> 23:19.710
Come back tonight.

23:20.189 --> 23:22.593
I'll take you to dinner after the show.

23:24.111 --> 23:25.589
I know you have a lot of questions,

23:25.614 --> 23:28.030
and I want to be able to answer them.

23:28.941 --> 23:30.858
Yeah. I don't think so.

23:30.883 --> 23:32.397
Please.

23:32.422 --> 23:34.567
♪♪

23:34.592 --> 23:35.843
- [KNOCK ON DOOR]
- Oh.

23:35.868 --> 23:37.679
JOSH: Alice, we need you.

23:37.704 --> 23:39.015
[DOOR OPENS]

23:39.040 --> 23:41.185
[SNIFFLES]

23:41.210 --> 23:42.905
[DOOR CLOSES]

23:44.315 --> 23:47.038
♪♪

23:47.063 --> 23:48.921
Looks like Grandma cleaned up.

23:48.946 --> 23:50.023
- [CHUCKLES]
- [CASH REGISTER BEEPS]

23:50.047 --> 23:51.382
I mean, am I even Grandma?

23:51.407 --> 23:53.889
Oh, my God. I knew you would do this.

23:53.914 --> 23:56.267
I knew you would find a
way to make this about you.

23:56.292 --> 23:58.100
How is this <i>not</i> about me?

23:58.125 --> 24:00.764
You just said that you want a child
that's part of <i>your</i> community,

24:00.789 --> 24:02.538
which is telling me that I'm not.

24:02.784 --> 24:05.475
Why don't I just go
ahead and wrap these up?

24:05.641 --> 24:06.694
Thank you.

24:06.719 --> 24:08.572
Mom, you know how hard it was for me

24:08.597 --> 24:10.819
being one of the only
black girls where we lived.

24:10.844 --> 24:12.710
Do you remember when you
took me to your salon

24:12.735 --> 24:14.202
and they tried to relax my hair,

24:14.227 --> 24:16.647
and they fried it so badly,
they had to chop it all off?

24:16.672 --> 24:18.577
You know I felt awful about that.

24:18.602 --> 24:19.819
Your father had just left.

24:19.844 --> 24:21.210
I know, but it was hard enough

24:21.235 --> 24:22.975
going to an all-white girls' school,

24:23.000 --> 24:24.702
and then after having to explain

24:24.727 --> 24:26.304
what happened to my hair...

24:26.329 --> 24:28.218
- Just... Ugh.
- Oh, well, please forgive me

24:28.243 --> 24:30.944
for wanting to give my daughter
the best opportunities.

24:31.915 --> 24:33.819
Regina, when
your father and I got married,

24:33.844 --> 24:36.100
it was the late '70s.

24:36.125 --> 24:38.038
We were young and idealistic.

24:38.063 --> 24:39.725
I didn't see color,

24:39.750 --> 24:41.895
and I didn't think anyone
else should either.

24:41.920 --> 24:43.265
I thought it would be easier for <i>you</i>

24:43.289 --> 24:44.460
if I raised you that way.

24:44.485 --> 24:46.155
Except the world isn't like that, Mom.

24:46.180 --> 24:48.608
It just... [SLAPS COUNTER] isn't.

24:49.836 --> 24:53.671
You may not see color,
but I don't have that privilege.

24:55.580 --> 24:58.280
I know you did the best you could.

24:59.090 --> 25:02.866
Well, apparently... it wasn't enough.

25:02.891 --> 25:04.218
Was it?

25:04.614 --> 25:06.554
- Anything else?
- [CASH REGISTER BEEPS]

25:08.040 --> 25:09.554
I think we're done here.

25:12.760 --> 25:15.382
[ <i>NE-HI'S "STAY YOUNG" PLAYS</i> ]

25:15.407 --> 25:17.061
I just keep thinking,

25:17.086 --> 25:18.939
what if she <i>didn't</i> leave?

25:19.168 --> 25:21.569
What if she saw me
playing in the street,

25:21.594 --> 25:23.194
got out of her car?

25:23.219 --> 25:24.421
[SCOFFS]

25:24.446 --> 25:26.374
What would you have done?

25:26.399 --> 25:28.647
I'd like to think I would
have yelled in her face.

25:28.672 --> 25:29.816
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

25:29.841 --> 25:31.921
Told her off for abandoning us.

25:32.689 --> 25:36.475
Really, I think I...
would've just hugged her.

25:36.500 --> 25:38.764
♪ <i>I've been holding to youth</i> ♪

25:38.789 --> 25:41.093
But she didn't even get out of the car.

25:41.678 --> 25:44.600
The one person that's supposed
to love me no matter what...

25:44.625 --> 25:45.733
didn't.

25:48.321 --> 25:51.788
No wonder it was so hard for you
to believe anyone else would.

25:51.813 --> 25:53.452
Till Maggie.

25:54.069 --> 25:55.780
[CHUCKLES]

25:55.805 --> 25:59.718
I finally opened myself up,
just to get burned again.

25:59.743 --> 26:04.147
Or maybe when you sensed
some uncertainty on her part,

26:04.172 --> 26:06.466
you... <i>you</i> pushed her away...

26:07.537 --> 26:09.682
... before she could hurt you?

26:10.074 --> 26:11.551
Mm.

26:11.576 --> 26:13.733
Mm. [CHUCKLES]

26:17.383 --> 26:20.085
I just... When I... When I see
the poster of this movie,

26:20.110 --> 26:22.014
- I j... I just see your...
- Todd!

26:22.983 --> 26:25.952
[CHUCKLING] Oh, snap.

26:25.977 --> 26:28.405
Yo, it's crazy running into you here.

26:28.430 --> 26:29.569
[STAMMERS]

26:29.594 --> 26:32.038
Yeah. Yeah. I-It is crazy.

26:32.063 --> 26:33.405
What up, Black man? Big fan.

26:33.430 --> 26:34.436
Ah, thanks. Isaac.

26:34.461 --> 26:35.710
- Good to meet you.
- You, too.

26:35.735 --> 26:37.726
Me and this dude go all the
way back to film school.

26:37.750 --> 26:40.061
Back when I had hair.
Ain't that right, Todd?

26:40.086 --> 26:41.991
[SIGHS] Yeah. That's right.

26:42.016 --> 26:44.272
You have been blowing up.

26:44.297 --> 26:46.686
Heard about the "Unseen" deal. Congrats.

26:46.711 --> 26:48.296
Thank you. Thank you.

26:48.321 --> 26:49.983
Seafood tower.

26:50.565 --> 26:52.936
Shoot. He must really
want you for this part.

26:53.863 --> 26:55.375
Look, it's always great
seeing you, Rome,

26:55.399 --> 26:57.172
but Isaac and I were kind of
in the middle of something.

26:57.196 --> 26:58.796
So, I... I'll call you, okay?

26:58.821 --> 27:00.069
No worries. No worries.

27:00.094 --> 27:01.288
All good. All good.

27:01.313 --> 27:03.186
I just need another minute of your time.

27:04.101 --> 27:06.460
Do you know why I didn't take your note

27:06.485 --> 27:08.202
to turn the suicide attempt in my script

27:08.227 --> 27:09.960
into a sports injury?

27:09.985 --> 27:11.906
Come on, Rome. I am trying
to have a meeting here...

27:11.930 --> 27:13.408
I didn't take your note
because those guys

27:13.432 --> 27:16.155
didn't come together
over a sports injury.

27:16.420 --> 27:18.155
We came together because my best friend

27:18.180 --> 27:19.382
jumped from a building

27:19.407 --> 27:21.686
just as I was about
to overdose on pills.

27:22.497 --> 27:25.405
That's right. I tried to kill myself.

27:25.430 --> 27:26.702
[SIGHS]

27:26.727 --> 27:28.983
So, yeah, Todd, suicide is real to me.

27:29.008 --> 27:31.654
Depression is real to me.

27:31.679 --> 27:33.069
[INHALES SHARPLY, SIGHS]

27:33.094 --> 27:34.114
I was trying to tell a story

27:34.138 --> 27:37.145
about how my friend dying saved my life,

27:37.170 --> 27:38.411
and <i>he</i> tried to take that from me.

27:38.435 --> 27:41.090
But then I realized you
can't steal my story.

27:42.983 --> 27:45.348
Because the real story is mine.

27:45.373 --> 27:49.449
♪♪

27:49.474 --> 27:50.520
[SIGHS]

27:50.545 --> 27:51.949
Sorry to interrupt your meeting.

27:52.067 --> 27:53.248
Later.

27:53.273 --> 27:54.842
The shrimp is really delish.

27:54.867 --> 27:57.905
Could use a pop of lemon,
but other than that, bangin'.

27:57.930 --> 28:02.349
♪♪

28:02.374 --> 28:04.352
- [SIGHS]
- [KNOCK ON DOOR]

28:04.563 --> 28:06.667
[SNIFFLES]

28:07.034 --> 28:08.703
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

28:10.879 --> 28:12.003
[SCOFFS]

28:12.074 --> 28:14.597
You're kidding me. Go away!

28:14.622 --> 28:16.456
Maggie, please, let me explain.

28:16.481 --> 28:18.777
You lied to me about
having my brother's heart!

28:18.802 --> 28:21.322
There is nothing you can say
that would make this okay!

28:21.347 --> 28:23.269
I-I-I know losing Chad destroyed you...

28:23.294 --> 28:25.527
Don't you dare say his name!

28:26.072 --> 28:28.508
Maggie, just listen to me, please.

28:28.533 --> 28:31.378
I know the day you lost him
was the worst day of your life.

28:31.403 --> 28:33.355
- Well, the day I lost Chloe
- [SNIFFLES]

28:33.380 --> 28:35.003
was the worst day of mine.

28:35.639 --> 28:37.003
We'd just gotten engaged.

28:37.028 --> 28:40.081
I'd surprised her with this
trip to Martha's Vineyard.

28:40.106 --> 28:44.294
In that moment with her,
I-I realized how lucky I was.

28:44.319 --> 28:47.691
She and I had something we
never thought we'd have.

28:48.270 --> 28:49.824
And that's the moment

28:49.849 --> 28:51.869
when I didn't see the bend in the road

28:51.894 --> 28:53.613
until it was too late.

28:54.795 --> 28:56.700
MAN: Went ahead and notified
General of the transport.

28:56.724 --> 28:58.230
I could barely move.

28:58.255 --> 28:59.950
MAN: Not getting any vitals.
Ready to move him out.

28:59.974 --> 29:02.722
I had this thing around my neck,
so I couldn't see much,

29:02.747 --> 29:05.105
but when I saw the red
and white lights, I...

29:05.130 --> 29:06.136
Get plasma, stat!

29:06.161 --> 29:07.808
- ... I knew.
- Chloe!

29:09.943 --> 29:11.144
And the worst part is,

29:11.169 --> 29:13.519
she shouldn't even
have been there with me.

29:13.544 --> 29:16.011
MAN: 25-year-old male,
Level 1 trauma activation.

29:16.036 --> 29:17.847
Weak pulse, possible internal bleeding.

29:17.872 --> 29:19.683
Please step out of the way, sir.

29:19.708 --> 29:21.199
I didn't realize it until later,

29:21.224 --> 29:23.059
- but your mom was in the hospital.
- PATRICIA: Where's my son?

29:23.083 --> 29:24.380
Where's my son? I'm looking for my son.

29:24.404 --> 29:26.138
- DOCTOR: Ma'am, calm down.
- Where is my son?

29:26.162 --> 29:27.840
- Are you Ms. Bloom?
- Yeah.

29:27.865 --> 29:29.676
I'm looking for my son, Chad.

29:30.080 --> 29:32.286
I'm sorry. We did everything we could.

29:32.311 --> 29:33.311
What?

29:33.336 --> 29:35.403
But he suffered from
severe brain damage.

29:35.428 --> 29:37.328
- No, he's not. He... He can't...
- I'm sorry.

29:37.353 --> 29:39.305
He's not brain-damaged.
He's gonna be okay.

29:39.330 --> 29:40.705
- No, no, no, no. It's okay.
- No, he's not!

29:40.729 --> 29:42.982
♪♪

29:43.007 --> 29:44.099
Good news, bad news.

29:44.124 --> 29:46.693
Uh, they were out of root beer, but...

29:46.923 --> 29:48.716
[GASPS] Orange soda!

29:48.741 --> 29:50.896
Hey! You spoil me.

29:50.921 --> 29:53.108
Play your cards right,
you might get some jello later.

29:53.133 --> 29:55.138
- Ooh.
- [PAGER BEEPS]

29:58.596 --> 30:00.242
Is that...

30:00.267 --> 30:01.857
[CHUCKLES]

30:01.882 --> 30:03.521
Oh, my God.

30:03.546 --> 30:04.810
You're getting a heart, baby.

30:04.836 --> 30:06.146
Really?

30:08.708 --> 30:10.880
ERIC: Chloe was the one who
got your brother's heart.

30:13.044 --> 30:14.693
- Hey. Okay.
- Wish me luck.

30:14.718 --> 30:16.193
See you soon, Tin Man.

30:16.781 --> 30:18.902
- I love you.
- I love you, too.

30:18.927 --> 30:20.108
[VOICE BREAKING] The best day of my life

30:20.132 --> 30:22.102
was the worst day of yours.

30:22.127 --> 30:24.669
[SNIFFLES]

30:24.694 --> 30:28.169
Because of Chad,
Chloe got six more years.

30:28.194 --> 30:29.630
But she should have had more.

30:29.655 --> 30:32.114
She should have had... a lifetime,

30:32.139 --> 30:35.575
and she would have,
if it... it wasn't for me.

30:37.412 --> 30:40.357
And then I got your mother's letter.

30:40.382 --> 30:41.575
The donor network sent it.

30:41.600 --> 30:42.966
They didn't know Chloe died.

30:42.991 --> 30:45.325
I opened it, and the... [SIGHS]

30:46.148 --> 30:49.029
the way your mother described her grief

30:49.340 --> 30:51.989
and her emptiness after Chad,

30:52.014 --> 30:54.693
that darkness, I...

30:54.718 --> 30:57.349
I felt the same thing.

30:58.305 --> 31:01.607
And then she mentioned you,
that you were sick.

31:01.632 --> 31:02.818
[SNIFFLES]

31:02.843 --> 31:04.696
I... I had to respond.

31:04.721 --> 31:06.919
So, you lied to her?

31:11.081 --> 31:12.529
I couldn't bring myself to tell her

31:12.554 --> 31:15.224
what happened to her son's heart.

31:15.249 --> 31:18.228
I thought I could
just... write a letter.

31:18.253 --> 31:20.023
I never meant for it to go this far.

31:20.048 --> 31:22.177
I never meant to come
between your family,

31:22.202 --> 31:25.880
and I am <i>so</i> sorry that I did.

31:25.905 --> 31:28.833
But, Maggie, you have to know, I...

31:29.309 --> 31:33.107
I wanted to tell you
the truth so many times.

31:33.132 --> 31:34.904
And I knew I needed to. I knew it.

31:34.929 --> 31:36.122
I-I did.

31:36.147 --> 31:37.576
But then the more time I spent with you,

31:37.600 --> 31:39.119
I just... I wanted more time,

31:39.144 --> 31:40.997
and then...

31:41.022 --> 31:43.060
you kissed me,

31:43.085 --> 31:45.044
and I knew I couldn't.

31:45.799 --> 31:50.107
In that moment, I just...
I just knew I-I never could,

31:50.132 --> 31:52.279
and not just because I
didn't want to hurt you,

31:52.304 --> 31:53.771
but because...

31:54.781 --> 31:56.661
I love you.

31:56.686 --> 31:58.982
♪♪

31:59.007 --> 32:01.349
Before I met you,
I-I couldn't see anything

32:01.374 --> 32:02.974
but my grief.

32:02.999 --> 32:04.568
You changed that.

32:04.593 --> 32:07.906
And I-I know that I lied, but I...

32:08.639 --> 32:09.841
I just needed you to know

32:09.866 --> 32:13.880
that my feelings f-for you,
our... our connection...

32:13.905 --> 32:16.888
That... that was real.

32:16.913 --> 32:23.913
♪♪

32:24.528 --> 32:26.216
Goodbye, Maggie.

32:27.326 --> 32:34.326
♪♪

32:35.538 --> 32:38.474
- [CELLPHONE VIBRATES]
- Jane Doe.

32:38.981 --> 32:40.364
Hello?

32:40.538 --> 32:43.146
Rome. Hey. Isaac Martin.

32:43.171 --> 32:44.911
- Oh. Hey.
- <i>I hope it's cool.</i>

32:44.936 --> 32:46.685
I got your number from Todd's assistant.

32:46.710 --> 32:49.685
[CHUCKLES] I gotta say,
that was a beast of a move.

32:49.995 --> 32:51.771
That dude...

32:51.796 --> 32:54.193
I just didn't feel like
I had much to lose.

32:54.218 --> 32:55.599
<i>That's actually why I'm calling.</i>

32:55.624 --> 32:56.904
I like "Unseen,"

32:56.929 --> 32:59.286
but I always felt like
something was missing.

32:59.311 --> 33:01.239
And after seeing you bum-rush Todd,

33:01.264 --> 33:02.888
I get the feeling that what's missing

33:02.913 --> 33:03.989
is your voice.

33:04.014 --> 33:05.607
<i>You open to sending me your script?</i>

33:05.632 --> 33:07.716
Wait, for real? D-Dude, say no more.

33:07.741 --> 33:08.872
I got you. Done.

33:08.897 --> 33:10.943
But hey... you should know

33:10.968 --> 33:12.857
it's not exactly financed or anything.

33:12.882 --> 33:13.903
Good. Good.

33:13.928 --> 33:16.294
I'm actually looking for
the right thing to produce.

33:16.319 --> 33:17.919
<i>Maybe we could put something together.</i>

33:17.944 --> 33:19.474
That would be...

33:19.499 --> 33:20.747
[CHUCKLING] Hells yeah.

33:20.772 --> 33:22.614
<i>I'll have my assistant reach out.</i>

33:22.639 --> 33:23.693
Guys like Todd

33:23.718 --> 33:26.208
have been stealing
our stories for years.

33:27.401 --> 33:29.661
Well, let's not let them
steal another one.

33:31.046 --> 33:33.089
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

33:37.038 --> 33:40.107
I saw what happened today,
with the hostess.

33:40.132 --> 33:42.099
[SCOFFS] Okay. Do you want to...

33:42.124 --> 33:43.733
- ... come in?
- And with that saleswoman, too.

33:43.757 --> 33:47.380
How you had to make sure that
she knew I was your mother.

33:47.405 --> 33:48.849
I know you thought I didn't notice,

33:48.874 --> 33:50.154
but I did.

33:50.179 --> 33:51.823
I notice more than you think.

33:51.848 --> 33:53.521
So, why didn't you say anything?

33:53.546 --> 33:54.655
Because I thought it would be better

33:54.679 --> 33:56.614
just to pretend like it didn't happen.

33:56.887 --> 33:58.146
But what you said

33:58.171 --> 34:00.904
about not having that privilege...

34:01.773 --> 34:03.286
I get that.

34:03.727 --> 34:06.091
And I get why you wouldn't
want that confusion

34:06.116 --> 34:07.505
for your child.

34:08.011 --> 34:09.822
T-Thank you for saying that.

34:09.847 --> 34:11.938
I realize I've done that my whole life.

34:11.963 --> 34:14.054
Just... Just skating past the bad

34:14.080 --> 34:15.679
to get to the good.

34:15.958 --> 34:18.601
Pretending the world
is better than it is.

34:22.335 --> 34:23.478
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

34:23.504 --> 34:26.302
Honey, I turned a cheek
to so many things...

34:27.748 --> 34:30.529
because I thought it
would be easier for you.

34:30.554 --> 34:33.208
But now I get how wrong that was.

34:35.443 --> 34:37.400
I let you down, Gina.

34:37.425 --> 34:38.833
I know that.

34:40.351 --> 34:43.029
That's why I was so happy today.

34:43.181 --> 34:44.994
Because deep down, I always thought

34:45.018 --> 34:47.614
that the reason you didn't want children

34:47.639 --> 34:49.146
was because of <i>me.</i>

34:50.172 --> 34:52.984
Because <i>I</i> didn't
set a good enough example.

34:54.646 --> 34:56.043
It's...

34:56.068 --> 34:58.021
But starting now,

34:58.046 --> 34:59.349
I just hope I can be

34:59.374 --> 35:01.779
half the mother I know you're gonna be.

35:03.093 --> 35:04.755
Thank you, Mom.

35:05.919 --> 35:07.522
[SNIFFLES] Yeah.

35:07.547 --> 35:08.858
You're gonna be one hell of a grandma.

35:08.882 --> 35:10.360
[CHUCKLES] Oh, sweetie.

35:10.385 --> 35:11.849
[CHUCKLES] Oh, honey.

35:11.874 --> 35:13.216
Oh.

35:13.241 --> 35:15.052
I really prefer "Nana."

35:15.077 --> 35:17.005
[BOTH LAUGH]

35:17.030 --> 35:19.279
[HUMMING]

35:19.304 --> 35:23.427
♪♪

35:23.452 --> 35:24.954
Hey.

35:27.652 --> 35:28.935
You're here.

35:28.960 --> 35:30.380
Yeah.

35:30.594 --> 35:33.411
Um, I'm really glad
you changed your mind.

35:34.781 --> 35:37.107
So, uh, do you like...

35:37.365 --> 35:39.091
pierogies? [CHUCKLES]

35:39.116 --> 35:40.685
Yeah, I mean, anything fried.

35:40.710 --> 35:42.286
- [CLEARS THROAT]
- Great.

35:42.311 --> 35:44.700
- Let's do it. [CHUCKLES]
- [LAUGHING] Okay.

35:45.505 --> 35:47.411
You'll love this place.

35:47.639 --> 35:49.833
Alice. He picked them up.

35:49.858 --> 35:51.552
Mark Dunnigan picked up the tickets.

35:51.577 --> 35:53.179
Oh! [LAUGHS]

35:53.204 --> 35:54.833
[BOTH LAUGH]

35:54.858 --> 35:56.466
Who's Mark Dunnigan?

35:56.491 --> 35:57.904
Uh, he's...

35:57.929 --> 36:00.302
one of the biggest
producers in the city.

36:00.327 --> 36:02.263
"Violet Moon," "Inside the Outside,"

36:02.288 --> 36:03.818
"The Seventh Floor." I...

36:03.843 --> 36:05.872
I mean, this could be like "Hamilton,"

36:05.897 --> 36:07.583
where they went from doing a workshop

36:07.608 --> 36:08.755
to going to the public,

36:08.780 --> 36:10.583
and then they went...

36:10.989 --> 36:12.927
to Broadway. [LAUGHS]

36:12.952 --> 36:14.596
We should take him for drinks,

36:14.621 --> 36:16.708
pitch him our vision for expanding it.

36:16.733 --> 36:19.279
Absolutely, uh, but I...

36:19.979 --> 36:21.721
[SIGHS]

36:21.746 --> 36:23.377
I'm...

36:24.414 --> 36:26.059
No, you should go.

36:26.738 --> 36:29.393
Are you sure? [CHUCKLES]

36:29.418 --> 36:30.799
Yeah.

36:30.824 --> 36:32.174
Because that would be great.

36:32.199 --> 36:35.213
Because... [SIGHS] this could be so big.

36:35.238 --> 36:37.651
But we can still do, uh, a dinner

36:37.676 --> 36:40.946
the next time... you're in town, okay?

36:40.971 --> 36:43.341
My God. Make sure that
you tell, um, Greg about the por...

36:43.366 --> 36:44.677
Um, the porch... porch scene.

36:44.702 --> 36:46.981
But... Yeah... Yeah, porch... Okay.

36:48.568 --> 36:49.997
Break a leg, Mom.

36:50.022 --> 36:51.755
Oh.

36:52.893 --> 36:54.075
Oh.

36:54.100 --> 36:56.661
♪♪

36:56.686 --> 36:59.005
[CHUCKLES]

36:59.030 --> 37:00.507
Okay.

37:00.532 --> 37:04.528
♪♪

37:07.902 --> 37:11.270
I'm so sorry. I-I shouldn't
have pushed you to come here.

37:11.295 --> 37:13.919
No. Don't be sorry.

37:13.944 --> 37:15.895
[CHUCKLES]

37:15.920 --> 37:17.333
I've spent so much time

37:17.358 --> 37:19.880
blaming myself for her leaving.

37:20.393 --> 37:22.270
I always thought...

37:22.969 --> 37:25.325
if I had been better,

37:25.350 --> 37:26.919
I'd been shinier,

37:26.944 --> 37:29.153
if I had just been more...

37:29.952 --> 37:31.270
I don't know.

37:31.724 --> 37:34.203
Then maybe she would've stuck around.

37:34.837 --> 37:36.849
Gary, what your mom did, it...

37:36.874 --> 37:38.497
It wasn't about you.

37:38.522 --> 37:40.667
I know. It was always about her.

37:40.692 --> 37:41.864
Huh.

37:42.287 --> 37:44.122
I see that now.

37:44.569 --> 37:46.083
I'm sorry, man.

37:46.108 --> 37:47.778
Don't be.

37:47.975 --> 37:50.028
You both are my family,

37:50.724 --> 37:52.028
and I'm sorry

37:52.053 --> 37:54.169
for not treating you like it lately.

37:54.622 --> 37:56.496
- It's all good.
- Yeah.

37:56.521 --> 37:58.207
[SIREN CHIRPS]

37:58.232 --> 37:59.341
Huh?

37:59.366 --> 38:01.560
Gary... your ride's here.

38:01.585 --> 38:02.729
[SNORTS]

38:02.754 --> 38:05.188
[ROME AND DELILAH LAUGH]

38:05.213 --> 38:06.993
[LAUGHS]

38:07.018 --> 38:08.313
[YAWNING] Alright.

38:08.338 --> 38:10.360
- Alright. [SIGHS]
- Sweet dreams.

38:10.628 --> 38:13.243
You know, I always say
that you're like a sister to me.

38:13.268 --> 38:14.290
Mm.

38:14.315 --> 38:15.959
But today, you were more of a mother

38:15.984 --> 38:17.438
than Alice ever was.

38:17.463 --> 38:18.735
- [CHUCKLES]
- Hey.

38:20.090 --> 38:22.234
Your children will never live in a world

38:22.259 --> 38:24.237
where their mother doesn't
get out of the car.

38:24.262 --> 38:27.165
As you may recall,
I've made some missteps of my own.

38:27.684 --> 38:29.509
I mean it, D.

38:29.649 --> 38:31.449
You're the best mom I know.

38:33.143 --> 38:35.118
Sophie's gonna come around.

38:37.387 --> 38:38.739
[CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

38:38.764 --> 38:40.165
- Yeah.
- Look at that.

38:41.364 --> 38:42.915
[BEEP]

38:42.940 --> 38:44.923
Hey, Maggie, can I call you ba...

38:45.747 --> 38:47.228
What's wrong?

38:47.253 --> 38:49.923
♪♪

38:49.948 --> 38:52.241
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

38:53.914 --> 38:55.625
[SIGHS]

39:00.232 --> 39:01.642
Hey.

39:02.479 --> 39:04.173
Hi.

39:06.850 --> 39:08.370
[SIGHS]

39:08.972 --> 39:11.450
[SNIFFLES] How much
did Delilah tell you?

39:11.522 --> 39:13.009
Enough.

39:15.116 --> 39:16.774
I'm sorry.

39:16.799 --> 39:23.799
♪♪

39:23.824 --> 39:28.602
♪♪

39:28.627 --> 39:31.424
I am such an idiot. [SNIFFLES]

39:32.546 --> 39:34.049
The whole time, he was lying,

39:34.074 --> 39:35.611
and I believed him.

39:35.636 --> 39:37.614
Hey, you didn't do anything wrong.

39:37.639 --> 39:40.861
You were really sad,
and you missed your brother.

39:40.886 --> 39:43.740
And if we're being
completely honest here,

39:43.765 --> 39:45.743
part of this is on me.

39:45.768 --> 39:46.768
Why?

39:46.793 --> 39:49.573
If I hadn't been so
insensitive about the psychic,

39:50.073 --> 39:51.909
your need for closure...

39:53.023 --> 39:55.049
I didn't give you what you needed.

39:55.932 --> 39:59.510
So, you had to go get it from... Eric.

39:59.535 --> 40:01.143
Gary, this is not on you.

40:01.168 --> 40:02.854
Maybe, but...

40:03.616 --> 40:05.432
it's not on you, either.

40:05.457 --> 40:09.034
♪♪

40:09.059 --> 40:10.956
Have you had dinner?

40:11.145 --> 40:13.123
I was gonna go...

40:13.148 --> 40:16.018
get tacos at that place down the street.

40:16.043 --> 40:18.120
♪♪

40:18.145 --> 40:20.292
No, I can't do that.

40:21.486 --> 40:23.573
I just...

40:24.573 --> 40:26.884
I just wanted to come here and tell you

40:26.909 --> 40:30.643
that I could've handled myself better.

40:30.668 --> 40:34.354
♪♪

40:34.379 --> 40:35.838
Good night.

40:35.863 --> 40:41.300
♪♪

40:41.325 --> 40:43.303
[SIGHS]

40:43.328 --> 40:50.328
♪♪

40:50.353 --> 40:57.353
♪♪

40:57.378 --> 41:01.062
♪♪
